Obesity Child's Daily Menu: No Breakfast and Dinner Embedded
More than one-third of children aged 9 to 13 have overweight problems, where overweight affects 9% of school population and 5% obesity.
Obesity children proceed mostly from families with a lifestyle that is unhealthy, according to current research.
It is again demonstrated the importance of the environment where it grows for a healthy development of the person, as well as the models that serve as a reference.
At the table, obsessive children are fed, for example, from built-ins at least twice as often as children from families with normal weight.
For dinner, more than 19% of the obese had dinner fried potatoes on the day before the analysis, which is linked to the prevention program "Obesity is not a chance."
In families of overweight children there is no custom to practice sports, which applies to most current families, where only 15% of children replied that their parents, at least once a week, find time for physical exercise.
Survey conducted to 900 children
The survey was conducted at the end of last school year and participated in the same nearly 900 children from Basic Education throughout the Czech Republic.
It was already the second edition of the program "The Obesity of Not is a Chance", which supports the General Health Insurance Company and Unilever.
So far, more than 12,000 children have participated in the project from the 4th to the 8th course.
A suitable diet and fairly family exercise are decisive factors, which significantly decrease the number of children with overweight and even obesity.
“Only half of the children surveyed have responded to have five meals daily according to the regime: breakfast, lunch, meal, lunch and dinner, which is one of the basic conditions for a healthy diet,” the survey said.
No breakfast but built-in for dinner
Specialists warn that in healthy development, details are also important, such as having a fixed hour for family breakfast.
In Czech Republic, however, only 23% of school families breakfast at the same time.
In most families, each breakfast alone.
But the worst thing was to discover that in 10% of households there is no breakfast.
Breakfast is, however, the basis for a proper daily diet.
The study shows that in families of obese children crazy potatoes are consumed much more often.
Almost everyone - regardless of weight - drinks daily sweet refreshments (70%).
Usually, more than 40% of children surveyed do sport, however, among their parents, this result is reduced to less than half, only 15%.
Fabricate your diet
The next phase of the study enabled the elected boys (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to create their own diets from all possible offers according to their tastes and opinions.
“The food preferences of Czech children in ages between 12 and 15, from the point of view of healthy food, are very far from the ideal.”
Among your favorite foods are pasta, meat and sweets.
"It's especially alarming the popularity of sweet refreshment," the study's final report states.
As a main food, the palm is taken the pasta and the bird meat follows it closely.
Practically, children always reject vegetables and the taste for fish and vegetables is very low.
Change to healthy habits
At the same time, the study shows that children are willing to change their eating habits if they receive fair information.
"In the control group of participants in the study, who filled the questionnaire after completing the prevention program "Obesity is not a coincidence," in many cases a significant change was given in favour of the principles of healthy eating."
Draw attention, for example, to sweet cooks, where many children would begin to prefer normal and current water.
Children would also more often choose bird meat and fish for main food and restrict the consumption of sweet food and flour derivatives.
