In Need for Speed: The Run competes throughout America.
Review
A trip, in principle unanswered, is complicated because of a series of improper carelessness of a routine trip during the tomorrow shift.
To some extent it was able to cover expectations, but this doesn't serve anything, if, in fact, it was not intended to do anything extraordinary.
The new delivery, which is added to the title The Run, awakened great expectations already before its premiere.
He promised that he would give new airs to the old race saga Need for Speed and, after shown, appears as a game that shouldn’t end up being a genre of action without any more.
We are also curious to know how the scenes would be inserted, where the main character descends from the car and walks on his own foot.
As it usually happens in the NFS series, the results don’t differ much from what we expected.
There are races that can be given for acceptable, but in the total computing points are lost because of absurd failures, which have already appeared in the series for years.
In fact, it cannot be called errors, but it is rather the incomprehensible mistake of developers.
The adventure begins very well.
You are introduced in a story, whose protagonist, Jack, has certain personal problems; to solve them, you are offered to participate in an illegal career throughout America.
You sit on the wheel at the west coast in San Francisco, and your mission is to get the first to New York.
The idea is to offer something interesting.
The route is divided into ten stages and then in more than fifty races.
This results in that each race takes place by a different route and the stages are located in different environments, which are quite diverse and interesting.
Thus, one doesn’t even have the feeling remotely that the game always offers the same.
Some of the environments are even pleasant at sight, although the technical level of the graph is equivalent to the previous deliveries of the series.
Therefore, it's nothing from the other world.
But the walk through the desert, the autumn landscape or the high snow-covered mountains produce a very pleasant visual effect.
In addition, races are diversifying from time to time by an atypical element.
Thus, for example, in the desert you find a sand storm that decreases visibility.
Instead, you must be careful in the mountains not to bury an avalanche.
According to that, each of the races is very well developed.
There are only a couple of models, but that’s enough.
For a moment, you try to advance a number of rivals required (normal in a classic race), then try to earn time (classical duel timed) and then await a duel against a single adversary.
In the middle of all this, sometimes the police appear, which doesn’t just make things even more difficult.
The newness is the landscapes outside the car.
Interactive animations are presented when Jack, in most cases, has to escape someone and you have to help him, always pressing the button right at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
It is surprising, however, that there are lots of fewer landscapes in the game than you could expect (in particular, there are only three).
But the final result is positive, because this element does not become annoying and, in the context already mentioned, it is one of the elements that make the game more interesting.
The driving model follows the footprints of the previous episodes.
That means that today it is no longer a big thing, but it cannot be claimed to be bad.
If you are looking for a realistic simulation, you can already look elsewhere.
But for a race designed with quite action, this style of driving is quite suitable for you, although we can find something better among the competition games.
Until here, everything in order.
But the problems arise after a while.
Unlike the right driving models, the same is no longer happening with collisions.
From this type of games it cannot be expected to recreate complicated deformations and collisions, but in fact before a blow against any object, you cannot predict how your car will react, with which not everything is in order.
It is typical that, by making a very tight advance or circulating the car with a normal traffic, there are only light sprays, but in other almost identical situations, your car ends up making uncontrolled piruetes.
Or even completely destroyed.
Thanks to the resete system, there are no major problems, but it can put you in bad mood.
The reset is scheduled in such a way that when you suffer an accident or leave the track, the game returns you to the last rescue point on the track.
In each race, however, there are only five races available.
If you consume them all, you have to restart the race from the beginning.
So it’s just a help in case something doesn’t go well, but it’s not too trustful.
Sometimes, neither reset helps, only helps learn the given stage of memory.
A big disadvantage of the game is that the same facts are repeated in different places.
In some curves, for example, you must enter in a specific way; otherwise, they are impossible to take.
Other times you find somewhere "civil" vehicles always with the same configuration, although you are the first, fifth, or arrive five minutes before or later.
This makes it anger especially in situations, when you see two cars going to meet in opposite directions, your opponent goes ahead without trouble, but when you arrive, you should rotate or either break.
It’s the same when you arrive, because it’s scheduled that the “surprise” will always happen in front of your noses.
The adversaries also have a further advantage.
Throughout the entire match you will reach places where, without taking into account the time, the same adversary will always ahead of you on the same site.
This also happens at the end of the match, on a long bridge, which is even more shocking.
Your opponent must arrive before you, at any price.
When it goes ahead of you, it makes the vision of the cars coming ahead of you, so at first you can wrap your car.
You can understand the idea of creating a game with maximum doses of suspense and adrenaline, but the execution is so apparent that you surely disappoint you immediately.
And it’s a pity, because even though the model of the journey is simple, the game is fun and with action, so it’s often not possible to follow detail what happens or where.
And it really doesn’t matter, whether merit takes the idea with fifty exclusive tracks or racing classification so that it doesn’t break boredom, or anything else.
An unusual idea is changing cars during the races.
You have to be attentive to gasoline suppliers next to the road, because exactly there you have to change your car, although in the vast majority of cases what you have is enough for you.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports are suitable for urban areas, American strong cars for straight highways and exotic supersports for technical driving, for example, by mountain roads with curves.
In addition, main narrative thread also appears a thread of parallel challenges, that is, there are races in specific places that you will know for stories.
Here you will not only get medals, but also experience points for your profile, which serves both for challenges and stories.
By reaching the upper level, the driver opens several possibilities, starting with the car and finishing with funds for the profile.
At the same time, an online Autolog feature is connected, which compares your results with those of other players and provides other community features.
One of the most difficult elements to understand is how the last race is done in history.
With the car you arrive to the metro tunnel (pass), where you get running in dark through the paths (pass).
The speed meter marks you between 150 and 200 km/h (pass) and suddenly behind you comes the metro convoy and takes you ahead without anything else.
In the writing we will certainly have a discussion about this for several days, about whether during the programming of the game none thought even a little bit, or whether the authors really take us for a panda of idiots.
The technical part of the game is nothing extraordinary, but at least the general visual effects result in most pleasant cases, sometimes even proud.
What a shame that, in the most tense moments, the image quality is reduced and sometimes in a serious way.
This mainly affects accidents where many participants are involved, when the continuous image quality is no longer valid.
The audio is fine and the soundtrack is a matter of tastes.
In order to be the pleasure of most of the youth group, the soundtrack belongs to the category "each of his father and mother", but it can be assumed that no one would buy the game alone for his music.
The final feeling of Need for Speed: The Run is quite confusing.
If the game avoided absolutely stupid mistakes, we would have trouble claiming that The Run is the best NFS game of recent years.
It gives the feeling that the game is not complete.
Fun is insured, but prepare because the mistakes will hit you in your eyes with the strength of some airport reflectors.
The choirs of the University of Carolina will participate in the "Students of Terciopelo" concert.
The joint celebration of the International Student Day and the anniversary of the Terciopelo Revolution as a musical experience will take place for the third time at the Festival Festa Academica.
During the same time, twenty corals of high schools and colleges will be presented.
The festival tours around two concerts on November 17.
“Carolina University has a high participation in the festival.”
