Innovative IBM starts its second century of existence
If someone looks for a term that highly accurately defines IBM’s strategy, the most approximate would be “long-term”.
For the general public, IBM is the symbol of a technological revolution, a company that is perceived as current and, however, has passed a hundred years since its foundation.
