He already covered the motto that many problems in the world have solutions if people are willing to think.
His motto "Think!" became his stamp, around which the life of the giant future will be built (it was also the title of an internal magazine that IBM began publishing in 1935).
Watson was also the foundation of a carefully raised company culture.
“For us, IBM involves a long-term thinking, a continuous movement towards the future.
IBM has survived and prospered for a hundred years for that reason, because it remained faithful to its basic principles, but without fear of the changes around it.
This has allowed us, during our first century, to transform technology, business and society.
