According to the PREP data, the difference between the first and second place of the governor’s election is just 27 percent, yet the votes corresponding to 879 of the 6,000 74 total records were not counted.
The possibility of counting "vote by vote" is a reality in terms of this year's election process in Michoacán, where according to the data drawn up by the Preliminary Election Results Program (PREP) the difference between the first and second place of the election of governor is just 27 percent, yet the votes corresponding to 879 of the 6,000 74 total acts are not counted.
In this regard, Chairman of the General Council of the Michoacán Electoral Institute (IEM), Maria of the Angels Llanderal Zaragoza, recalled that a few days ago, almost on 9 November, the electoral body approved a series of guidelines in order to harmonize local rules with federal electoral reform.
As it will be remembered, Michoacán did not approve its Political Constitution or its Electoral Code of the State or its Electoral Justice Act, whenever the Congress of the State approved the reforms shortly before completing the legal deadline for them to enter into force in this electoral process and Governor Leonel Godoy Rangel omitted its publication within the deadlines set out in the State Official Journal Act.
On 9 November, the Supreme Court of the Nation (SCJN) solved the constitutional dispute promoted by the local legislative power and called the state president's vote to constitutional reforms as "invalid and illegal", whenever he does not have the right to "repeal or vete them."
Interviewed about the possibility of "voting by vote", Maria of the Llanderal Angels explained that, thanks to the approval of the corresponding guidelines by the General Council of the IEM, partial and total counts of voting by the local electoral body will be possible.
Thus, the partial count of votes, of one or more vote packages, may occur in the assumptions that: the results of the acts do not coincide; there is no record of scrutiny and computing in the case of the box or does not work in the power of the president thereof; or, where there are obvious errors or alterations of the acts.
Furthermore, the total count of the vote received in all boxes of the election may be carried out when there is an indication that the difference between the alleged candidate winner of the election concerned and the candidate who has obtained the second place in the vote is equal to or less than one percentage point; provided that at the beginning of the meeting the express request of the representative of the party and/or to the candidate.
The total count of the vote may also be carried out if the difference between the allegedly winner candidate and the second place is equal to or lower to a percentage point, provided that there is an express request from the representative of the political party whose candidate remains second, in which the electoral packages that have been partially counted are excluded.
It should be mentioned that in such a situation is the election of Morelia, where according to the PREP the difference between the first and the second place is only 0.16 percent, although not counting the votes of 129 of the 923 total records.
