The European continent should be able to remember this because, although it was invented in Athens more than 2,000 years ago, over the twentieth century has suffered the tragedies of World War, totalitarism, Holocaust, Gulag, but also Franco in Spain, Salazar in Portugal, the coronels in Greece.
